hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a complex power series given by $\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} c_n (z - z_0)^n$, where $z$ is a complex variable and the center of the series is specified as $z_0 = 3 - 4i$. The coefficients $c_n$ of the series depend on whether the index $n$ is even or odd, according to the rule:
$$
c_n = \begin{cases}
    \left(\frac{n+1}{2n+5}\right)^n  \text{if } n \text{ is even} \\
    \left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^n  \text{if } n \text{ is odd}
\end{cases}
$$
Determine the radius of convergence, $R$, of this power series.
